title: Democracy in America Vol. I
creator: Alexis de Tocqueville
description: Librivox recording of Democracy in America Volume I by Alexis de Tocqueville. Read by LibriVox Volunteers. When Tocqueville visited America in the 1830s he found a thriving democracy of a kind he had not seen anywhere else. Many of his insightful observations American society and political system, found in the two volume book he published after his visit, still remain surprisingly relevant today. (Summary by the Bookworm) M4B audiobook of complete book For more free audiobooks, or to become a volunteer reader, please visit librivox.org.
subject: librivox; audiobooks; democracy; America; de Tocqueville; history; philosophy; politics
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
